{
    "chapter": 101,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "101:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>The Clattering Blow, the Resurrection that will make hearts clatter by its terrors.</p>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "101:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>What is the Clattering Blow? — [intended] to emphasise its awesomeness (m'l-qri`a: both of these [elements] constitute a subject and a predicate, and [together] the predicate of [the first] al-qri`a).</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "101:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And what will show you, [what] will make known to you, what the Clattering Blow is? — additional emphasis of its awesomeness (the first m is a subject, and what follows it is its predicate; the second m and its predicate also function together as the second direct object of [the verb] adr, `show').</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "101:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>The day (yawma: that which renders it accusative is [the verb] indicated by al-qri`a, in other words, [by the implied] taqra`u, `it clatters') mankind will be like scattered moths, like a throng of scattered locusts surging into each other in confusion, until they are summoned to the Reckoning,</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "101:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and the mountains will be like tufts of wool, like carded wool in terms of the lightness with which it floats [in the air] until it comes to settle upon the earth.</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "101:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Then as for him whose scales weigh heavy, in that his good deeds outweigh his misdeeds,</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "101:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>he will enjoy a pleasant life, in Paradise, that is to say, a pleasing one, for he will be pleased with it, that is, it will be pleasing to him;</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "101:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>but as for him whose scales weigh light, in that his evil deeds outweigh his good ones,</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "101:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>his home will be the Abyss.</h2>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "101:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And what will show you what it is?, that is to say, what the Abyss is.</p>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "101:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>It is: A scorching fire, of extremely hot temperature (the h' of hiya is for [consonantal] quiescence, and is retained when reciting without a [subsequent] pause or with; some omit it when reciting without a pause). Meccan, consisting of 8 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}